headlines.description: — The Cleveland Cavaliers are legit, and the defending NBA champions now know it, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Love scores 25, Cavs make 19 3s and stun champion Bucks

headlines.description: — Charlotte coach James Borrego gave his players a simple instruction Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets break franchise record with 158-126 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Luke Kennard scored 17 points, Amir Coffey added 15 and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied to defeat the Orlando Magic 111-102 on Wednesday, one night after they matched the second-largest comeback in NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally for 2nd straight night to top Magic, 111-102

headlines.description: — Bogdan Bogdanovic scored 18 points in his return from a knee injury, Onyeka Okongwu also had 18 off the bench and the Atlanta Hawks recovered from a slow start to beat the struggling Sacramento Kings 121-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic, Okongwu lead surging Hawks past Kings, 121-104

events.name: New York Knicks at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Duncan Robinson scored 25 points while shooting 7 of 11 from 3-point range, leading four Miami players with 20 or more points in the Heat’s 110-96 victory over the New York Knicks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson scores 25 to lead Heat to 110-96 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Denver Nuggets coach Michael Malone sensed his team would play down to a Brooklyn Nets team that was missing three of their best players, including All-Star guard James Harden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Rivers team up to help Nuggets top Nets, 124-118

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 29 points, Zach LaVine added 23 and the Chicago Bulls beat the Toronto Raptors 111-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan powers Bulls to 111-105 win over Raptors

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Ja Morant matched a season high with 41 points and the Memphis Grizzlies overcame Dejounte Murray’s 14th career triple-double — which tied a Spurs franchise record — by beating San Antonio 118-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Grizzlies spoil Murray's record, top Spurs 118-110

headlines.description: — When Chris Paul joined Devin Booker on the Phoenix Suns after a trade last season, it wasn’t always easy to decide who would be the finisher when games got tight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker leads Suns past Jazz 105-97 for 8th straight win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 15 points, 10 rebounds and 15 assists for his sixth triple-double this season, and the Dallas Mavericks led wire-to-wire in a 132-112 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's triple-double helps Dallas down Portland 132-112
